Dr. Yetman is also an accomplished author and photographer. His books
		include: 
	 Where the Desert Meets the Sea: A Trader in the Land of the Seri
		Indians; 
	 Sonora: An Intimate Geography; 
	 Gentry's Rio Mayo Plants: the Tropical Deciduous Forest and Environs
		of Northwest Mexico; 
	 Scattered Round Stones: A Mayo Village in Sonora, Mexico; 
	 Mayo Ethnobotany: Land History, and Traditional Knowledge in
		Northwest Mexico; and 
	 Hidden People: The Guarijíos of Northwest Mexico and their
		Ethnobotany
